<article class="py-16 sm:py-20 px-gutter"><div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose-bliss text-on-surface-variant text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
<p class="text-xl text-on-surface font-headline-sm leading-relaxed mb-8">Constipation affects people of all ages and responds best to a holistic, sustainable approach rather than relying on over-the-counter medication alone.</p>
<h2 class="font-headline-lg text-primary text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Understanding Constipation</h2><p>Constipation develops when bowel movements become infrequent or difficult. Common causes include low fibre intake, dehydration, sedentary habits, stress and irregular eating. Ignoring it can affect daily life and overall health, so it's important to treat the underlying causes rather than just the symptoms.</p>
<h2 class="font-headline-lg text-primary text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">A Thorough Strategy for Relief</h2><p>Lasting relief combines natural remedies, dietary guidance and lifestyle adjustments — increasing fibre-rich foods and hydration, regular exercise and yoga, Ayurvedic/homeopathic/naturopathic support, and detox programs such as colon hydrotherapy that reactivate natural peristalsis.</p>
<h2 class="font-headline-lg text-primary text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Ease Bloating with Restorative Massage</h2><p>Gentle lymphatic and abdominal massage techniques stimulate bowel movements, reduce bloating and improve digestive comfort — working best alongside dietary and lifestyle recommendations.</p>
<h2 class="font-headline-lg text-primary text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Benefits of Specialised Treatment</h2><p>Professional treatment offers personalised care, long-term relief focused on root causes, holistic wellness improvements and natural solutions that minimise reliance on harsh medications.</p>
<h2 class="font-headline-lg text-primary text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Lifestyle Advice to Reduce Constipation</h2><p>Drink around eight glasses of water daily, include probiotics, practise digestion-supporting yoga, eat high-fibre foods and eat mindfully to sustain long-term relief.</p>
</div></article>
